urlText: Buses replace trains between Cronulla, Waterfall and Central
content:
Saturday 12 and Sunday 13 December
  • Buses replace trains between Cronulla, Waterfall and Central. Some buses start and end at Redfern.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Bondi Junction and Central.
  • If you are travelling to T8 Airport & South Line stations, change at Central or catch bus 7AT4 to Wolli Creek and change for a T8 Airport & South Line train.

  • Banksia Station: Due to work on the pedestrian underpass at Banksia, a shuttle bus service will run between the Princes Highway and Railway St sides of the station to connect with bus route 7AT4.
  • Route 7AT4 buses towards Hurstville leave from Railway St, and buses towards Redfern leave from the Princes Highway.

  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
1T4: Cronulla, then all stations to Caringbah then Central and return
1AT4: Kirrawee, then all stations to Miranda then Central and return
2T4: Waterfall, then all stations to Sutherland then Central and return
2AT4: Sutherland, then all stations to Hurstville then Central and return
3AT4: Hurstville, then Central and return
5AT4: Kogarah, Rockdale then Redfern and return
6AT4: Cronulla, then all stations to Sutherland, Hurstville, then all stations to Rockdale, Tempe, Sydenham then Redfern and return
7AT4: Hurstville, then all stations to Redfern and return
17T4: Banksia Station shuttle bus Princes Highway to Railway St
subtitle: Buses replace trains between Cronulla, Waterfall and Central

urlText: T1 North Shore Line: Trackwork between North Sydney and Wynyard
content:
Friday 1 to Sunday 10 January
  • From 6am Friday 1 January, buses replace all trains between North Sydney and Wynyard.
  • Ferries also run between Milsons Point and Circular Quay wharves.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Hornsby and North Sydney only.
  • T9 Northern Line trains run between Berowra or Hornsby and Central, platforms 1-12, via Strathfield.
 Monday 4 to Friday 8 January
  • Trains run to a weekend timetable with extra trains during the morning and afternoon peak periods.
  • Daily from 6am until 7pm, express buses also run between North Sydney and Circular Quay (Macquarie St) or Town Hall (Bathurst St).
  • Check service capacity and allow extra travel time.
  • Plan ahead before you travel for up-to-date information.
